\f1 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Strangely enough, such an explanation divorces humanity from nature. It makes humans mysterious, radically discontinuous, opaque, anomalous, and queer. Since I am here assuming that humans are continuous with nature, I reject an account of teleology that makes it natural only to humans but unnatural to the cosmos as a whole. Furthermore, I have studiously avoided using too many uncontroversial examples of human normativity, preferring the more controversial (and hence more interesting) examples of non-human normative facts. \
